<subSubSection id="C359657F3673FFBC28D8FB28FC26958F" pageId="20" pageNumber="227" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFC36F43673FFBC28D8FB28FC26958F" blockId="20.[177,1085,1278,1447]" pageId="20" pageNumber="227">
Comment: This species was described from &quot; 
<collectingCountry id="F35476643673FFBC2AB5FB28FCB4953C" box="[732,797,1278,1300]" name="China" pageId="20" pageNumber="227">China</collectingCountry>
, Guandong, Da Wu Ling&quot; (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD24B053673FFBC28D0FACAFE99951A" author="PACE R" box="[185,304,1308,1330]" pageId="20" pageNumber="227" pagination="457 - 523" refId="ref22403" refString="PACE R. (2004): Hygronomini e Athetini della Cina con note sinonimiche (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Revue Suisse de Zoologie 111 (3): 457 - 523." type="journal article" year="2004">PACE 2004</bibRefCitation>
), based on a male 
<typeStatus id="54F888563673FFBC2991FACAFDF8951A" box="[504,593,1308,1330]" pageId="20" pageNumber="227">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<specimenCount id="9D45FD7D3673FFBC2AE1FACAFD52951A" box="[648,763,1308,1330]" pageId="20" pageNumber="227" type="female">two female</specimenCount>
<typeStatus id="54F888563673FFBC2B6CFACAFCC09519" box="[773,873,1308,1329]" pageId="20" pageNumber="227">paratypes</typeStatus>
. The examined type material is in rather poor condition. The 
<typeStatus id="54F888563673FFBC2A26FAEFFD019567" box="[591,680,1337,1359]" pageId="20" pageNumber="227">holotype</typeStatus>
has one elytron missing, its aedeagus is somewhat deformed, and the spermatheca of the 
<typeStatus id="54F888563673FFBC2AC1FA81FD569544" box="[680,767,1367,1388]" pageId="20" pageNumber="227">paratype</typeStatus>
is completely deformed. Since the description and illustrations provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD24B053673FFBC2AE8FAA2FCAA95A2" author="PACE R" box="[641,771,1396,1418]" pageId="20" pageNumber="227" pagination="457 - 523" refId="ref22403" refString="PACE R. (2004): Hygronomini e Athetini della Cina con note sinonimiche (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Revue Suisse de Zoologie 111 (3): 457 - 523." type="journal article" year="2004">PACE (2004)</bibRefCitation>
are incomplete and somewhat misleading, respectively, a redescription and new illustrations are given.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
