<emphasis id="B937EAE63672FFBD2901FA2BFED6963A" bold="true" box="[360,383,1533,1554]" pageId="21" pageNumber="228">69</emphasis>
) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (
<emphasis id="B937EAE63672FFBD2B65FA2BFC8A963A" bold="true" box="[780,803,1533,1554]" pageId="21" pageNumber="228">70</emphasis>
) apical portion of median lobe of aedeagus in ventral view; (
<emphasis id="B937EAE63672FFBD29ABF9C2FE709601" bold="true" box="[450,473,1556,1577]" pageId="21" pageNumber="228">71</emphasis>
) paramere; (
<emphasis id="B937EAE63672FFBD2A26F9C2FDCF9601" bold="true" box="[591,614,1556,1577]" pageId="21" pageNumber="228">72</emphasis>
) female tergite VIII; (
<emphasis id="B937EAE63672FFBD2B5BF9C2FCE09601" bold="true" box="[818,841,1556,1577]" pageId="21" pageNumber="228">73</emphasis>
) female sternite VIII; (
<emphasis id="B937EAE63672FFBD2C76F9C2FB9F9601" bold="true" box="[1055,1078,1556,1577]" pageId="21" pageNumber="228">74</emphasis>
) spermatheca. Scale bars: 65-66: 0.5 mm; 67-74: 0.2 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C359657F3671FFBE28DBFF0DFD7A945A" pageId="22" pageNumber="229" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BFC36F43671FFBE28DBFF0DFE7091AB" blockId="22.[178,1086,219,387]" pageId="22" pageNumber="229">
Redescription: Body length 
<quantity id="4CBB9B113671FFBE2A3DFF0DFD7B90D8" box="[596,722,219,241]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="3.3" pageId="22" pageNumber="229" unit="mm" value="3.9" valueMax="4.5" valueMin="3.3">3.3-4.5 mm</quantity>
; length of forebody 
<quantity id="4CBB9B113671FFBE2BD2FF0DFB9390D8" box="[955,1082,219,241]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="1.9" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="22" pageNumber="229" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="1.9" valueMin="1.6">1.6-1.9 mm</quantity>
. Coloration: head blackish-brown to blackish; pronotum dark-brown to blackish-brown; elytra brown to dark-brown; abdomen blackish-brown, with the anterior segments often slightly paler and with the posterior margins of the segements narrowly reddish to reddish-brown; legs yellowish; antennae reddish-brown with the basal 2-3 antennomeres and antennomere XI reddish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFC36F43671FFBE28DBFE44FB879212" blockId="22.[178,1085,402,571]" pageId="22" pageNumber="229">
Head (
<figureCitation id="13782A713671FFBE289FFE44FEE99180" box="[246,320,402,424]" captionStart="Figs 65-74" captionStartId="21.[178,218,1510,1532]" captionTargetBox="[182,1068,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-1@21.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 65-74: Nepalota fellowesi PACE: (65) forebody; (66) antenna; (67) male tergite VIII; (68) male sternite VIII; (69) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (70) apical portion of median lobe of aedeagus in ventral view; (71) paramere; (72) female tergite VIII; (73) female sternite VIII; (74) spermatheca. Scale bars: 65-66: 0.5 mm; 67-74: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414200" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414200/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="229">Fig. 65</figureCitation>
) weakly transverse; dorsal surface with distinct microreticulation and with very fine and sparse punctation. Eyes moderately large, slightly longer than postocular region in dorsal view. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13782A713671FFBE2A7AFE1BFDC891CB" box="[531,609,461,483]" captionStart="Figs 65-74" captionStartId="21.[178,218,1510,1532]" captionTargetBox="[182,1068,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-1@21.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 65-74: Nepalota fellowesi PACE: (65) forebody; (66) antenna; (67) male tergite VIII; (68) male sternite VIII; (69) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (70) apical portion of median lobe of aedeagus in ventral view; (71) paramere; (72) female tergite VIII; (73) female sternite VIII; (74) spermatheca. Scale bars: 65-66: 0.5 mm; 67-74: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414200" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414200/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="229">Fig. 66</figureCitation>
) slender, 
<quantity id="4CBB9B113671FFBE2AA6FE1BFCE391CA" box="[719,842,461,482]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="22" pageNumber="229" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="1.2">1.2-1.3 mm</quantity>
long; antennomere IV weakly oblong or approximately as long as broad; antennomeres V-X of gradually increasing width and increasingly transverse; preapical antennomeres moderately transverse; antennomere XI apically acute, slightly longer than the combined length of IX and X.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFC36F43671FFBE28DBFD9DFE2F92B3" blockId="22.[178,1085,586,667]" pageId="22" pageNumber="229">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="13782A713671FFBE2941FD9CFEDF9248" box="[296,374,586,608]" captionStart="Figs 65-74" captionStartId="21.[178,218,1510,1532]" captionTargetBox="[182,1068,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-1@21.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 65-74: Nepalota fellowesi PACE: (65) forebody; (66) antenna; (67) male tergite VIII; (68) male sternite VIII; (69) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (70) apical portion of median lobe of aedeagus in ventral view; (71) paramere; (72) female tergite VIII; (73) female sternite VIII; (74) spermatheca. Scale bars: 65-66: 0.5 mm; 67-74: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414200" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414200/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="229">Fig. 65</figureCitation>
) 1.20-1.25 times as broad as long and approximately 1.4 times as broad as head, without sexual dimorphism; disc with distinct microreticulation and with very fine punctation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFC36F43671FFBE28DBFD7CFB8D92F5" blockId="22.[178,1085,682,733]" pageId="22" pageNumber="229">
Elytra (
<figureCitation id="13782A713671FFBE2896FD7CFEE092E8" box="[255,329,682,704]" captionStart="Figs 65-74" captionStartId="21.[178,218,1510,1532]" captionTargetBox="[182,1068,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-1@21.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 65-74: Nepalota fellowesi PACE: (65) forebody; (66) antenna; (67) male tergite VIII; (68) male sternite VIII; (69) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (70) apical portion of median lobe of aedeagus in ventral view; (71) paramere; (72) female tergite VIII; (73) female sternite VIII; (74) spermatheca. Scale bars: 65-66: 0.5 mm; 67-74: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414200" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414200/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="229">Fig. 65</figureCitation>
) approximately 0.9 times as long as pronotum; punctation dense and fine; interstices with distinct microreticulation and subdued shine. Hind wings fully developed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFC36F43671FFBE28DBFD3AFD7A9372" blockId="22.[178,1085,748,858]" pageId="22" pageNumber="229">Abdomen with distinct transverse microsculpture; anterior portions of tergites III-VII impunctate; posterior portions of tergites III-V with moderately sparse, those of tergites VI-VII with very sparse punctation; pubescence predominantly composed of very thin setae; tergites III and VII without sexual dimorphism.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFC36F43671FFBE28DBFCBCFB8993DC" blockId="22.[178,1086,874,1013]" pageId="22" pageNumber="229">
♂: tergite VIII (
<figureCitation id="13782A713671FFBE290DFCBCFE1A93A8" box="[356,435,874,896]" captionStart="Figs 65-74" captionStartId="21.[178,218,1510,1532]" captionTargetBox="[182,1068,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-1@21.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 65-74: Nepalota fellowesi PACE: (65) forebody; (66) antenna; (67) male tergite VIII; (68) male sternite VIII; (69) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (70) apical portion of median lobe of aedeagus in ventral view; (71) paramere; (72) female tergite VIII; (73) female sternite VIII; (74) spermatheca. Scale bars: 65-66: 0.5 mm; 67-74: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414200" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414200/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="229">Fig. 67</figureCitation>
) approximately as long as broad and with distinctly convex posterior margin; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="13782A713671FFBE2990FC51FDEC93B5" box="[505,581,903,925]" captionStart="Figs 65-74" captionStartId="21.[178,218,1510,1532]" captionTargetBox="[182,1068,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-1@21.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 65-74: Nepalota fellowesi PACE: (65) forebody; (66) antenna; (67) male tergite VIII; (68) male sternite VIII; (69) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (70) apical portion of median lobe of aedeagus in ventral view; (71) paramere; (72) female tergite VIII; (73) female sternite VIII; (74) spermatheca. Scale bars: 65-66: 0.5 mm; 67-74: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414200" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414200/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="229">Fig. 68</figureCitation>
) oblong, somewhat longer than tergite VIII, and strongly convex posteriorly; median lobe of aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="13782A713671FFBE2A92FC72FCC69392" box="[763,879,932,954]" captionStart="Figs 65-74" captionStartId="21.[178,218,1510,1532]" captionTargetBox="[182,1068,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-1@21.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 65-74: Nepalota fellowesi PACE: (65) forebody; (66) antenna; (67) male tergite VIII; (68) male sternite VIII; (69) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (70) apical portion of median lobe of aedeagus in ventral view; (71) paramere; (72) female tergite VIII; (73) female sternite VIII; (74) spermatheca. Scale bars: 65-66: 0.5 mm; 67-74: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414200" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414200/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="229">Figs 69-70</figureCitation>
) approximately 
<quantity id="4CBB9B113671FFBE2C74FC72FF7093FF" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="229" unit="mm" value="0.6">0.6 mm</quantity>
long, conspicuously long and slender; paramere (
<figureCitation id="13782A713671FFBE2A8EFC17FC9D93F0" box="[743,820,961,984]" captionStart="Figs 65-74" captionStartId="21.[178,218,1510,1532]" captionTargetBox="[182,1068,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-1@21.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 65-74: Nepalota fellowesi PACE: (65) forebody; (66) antenna; (67) male tergite VIII; (68) male sternite VIII; (69) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (70) apical portion of median lobe of aedeagus in ventral view; (71) paramere; (72) female tergite VIII; (73) female sternite VIII; (74) spermatheca. Scale bars: 65-66: 0.5 mm; 67-74: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414200" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414200/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="229">Fig. 71</figureCitation>
) approximately 
<quantity id="4CBB9B113671FFBE2B88FC17FB9493FF" box="[993,1085,961,983]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="22" pageNumber="229" unit="mm" value="0.55">0.55 mm</quantity>
long, shorter than median lobe, and with slender apical lobe with two long black setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFC36F43671FFBE28DBFBDCFD7A945A" blockId="22.[178,1085,1028,1138]" pageId="22" pageNumber="229">
<specimenCount id="9D45FD7D3671FFBE28DBFBDCFF6E9437" box="[178,199,1034,1055]" pageId="22" pageNumber="229" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
: tergite VIII (
<figureCitation id="13782A713671FFBE290DFBD2FE1D9432" box="[356,436,1028,1050]" captionStart="Figs 65-74" captionStartId="21.[178,218,1510,1532]" captionTargetBox="[182,1068,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-1@21.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 65-74: Nepalota fellowesi PACE: (65) forebody; (66) antenna; (67) male tergite VIII; (68) male sternite VIII; (69) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (70) apical portion of median lobe of aedeagus in ventral view; (71) paramere; (72) female tergite VIII; (73) female sternite VIII; (74) spermatheca. Scale bars: 65-66: 0.5 mm; 67-74: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414200" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414200/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="229">Fig. 72</figureCitation>
) approximately as long as broad and with distinctly convex posterior margin; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="13782A713671FFBE2990FBF7FDED941F" box="[505,580,1057,1079]" captionStart="Figs 65-74" captionStartId="21.[178,218,1510,1532]" captionTargetBox="[182,1068,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-1@21.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 65-74: Nepalota fellowesi PACE: (65) forebody; (66) antenna; (67) male tergite VIII; (68) male sternite VIII; (69) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (70) apical portion of median lobe of aedeagus in ventral view; (71) paramere; (72) female tergite VIII; (73) female sternite VIII; (74) spermatheca. Scale bars: 65-66: 0.5 mm; 67-74: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414200" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414200/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="229">Fig. 73</figureCitation>
) moderately transverse and with broadly convex posterior margin, middle of posterior margin not concave; spermatheca (
<figureCitation id="13782A713671FFBE2B8AFBE8FB9F947D" box="[995,1078,1086,1109]" captionStart="Figs 65-74" captionStartId="21.[178,218,1510,1532]" captionTargetBox="[182,1068,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-1@21.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 65-74: Nepalota fellowesi PACE: (65) forebody; (66) antenna; (67) male tergite VIII; (68) male sternite VIII; (69) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (70) apical portion of median lobe of aedeagus in ventral view; (71) paramere; (72) female tergite VIII; (73) female sternite VIII; (74) spermatheca. Scale bars: 65-66: 0.5 mm; 67-74: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414200" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414200/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="229">Fig. 74</figureCitation>
) approximately 
<quantity id="4CBB9B113671FFBE2923FB8AFE3E9459" box="[330,407,1116,1137]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="229" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.4 mm</quantity>
long, with rather long capsule.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C359657F3671FFBE28DBFB5FFC6D9494" pageId="22" pageNumber="229" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFC36F43671FFBE28DBFB5FFC6D9494" blockId="22.[178,1085,1161,1212]" pageId="22" pageNumber="229">Comparative notes: This species is characterized particularly by the conspicuous shape and internal structures of the median lobe of the aedeagus.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C359657F3671FFBE28DBFB02FE599576" pageId="22" pageNumber="229" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BFC36F43671FFBE28DBFB02FE599576" blockId="22.[178,1086,1236,1375]" pageId="22" pageNumber="229">
Distribution and natural history: The known distribution is confined to one locality in 
<collectingRegion id="4987F8163671FFBE29AEFB27FD94952F" box="[455,573,1265,1287]" country="China" name="Guangdong" pageId="22" pageNumber="229">Guangdong</collectingRegion>
and one at the foot of Dawei 
<collectingRegion id="4987F8163671FFBE2B19FB27FC0A952F" box="[880,931,1265,1287]" country="Myanmar" name="Shan" pageId="22" pageNumber="229">Shan</collectingRegion>
near Pingbian, southeastern 
<collectingRegion id="4987F8163671FFBE295EFAD9FE2E950C" box="[311,391,1295,1316]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="22" pageNumber="229">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation id="13782A713671FFBE29FCFAD8FE70950C" box="[405,473,1294,1316]" captionStart="Map 3" captionStartId="7.[178,223,811,832]" captionTargetBox="[178,1082,212,801]" captionTargetId="figure-1@7.[178,1082,212,801]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Map 3: Distributions of Nepalota franzi PACE (filled circles), N. mocytoides nov.sp. (open circle), and N. fellowesi PACE (filled triangles), based on examined and reliable literature records." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414163" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414163/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="229">Map 3</figureCitation>
). The specimens from 
<collectingRegion id="4987F8163671FFBE2AABFAD9FCBB950C" box="[706,786,1295,1316]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="22" pageNumber="229">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
were sifted from leaf litter in a subtropical broad-leaved forest at an altitude of 
<quantity id="4CBB9B113671FFBE2B67FAFDFCC09569" box="[782,873,1323,1345]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="22" pageNumber="229" unit="m" value="1500.0">1500 m</quantity>
, together with 
<taxonomicName id="4C434D773671FFBE2C4FFAFAFEFF9576" authorityName="PACE" authorityYear="2004" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Nepalota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="229" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guangdongensis">
<emphasis id="B937EAE63671FFBE2C4FFAFAFEFF9576" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="229">N. guangdongensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C434D773671FFBE29EEFA9FFE439576" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2015" box="[391,490,1353,1374]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Nepalota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="229" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crocea">
<emphasis id="B937EAE63671FFBE29EEFA9FFE439576" box="[391,490,1353,1374]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="229">N. crocea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
